[19]
Apotex does not dispute that their proposed tablets of sildenafil citrate would be infringing if the patent is valid in the sense that issuance of the prohibition order is justified. Validity in the context of these proceedings is limited to the scope of the
Regulations
. The issues raised by Apotex's NOA and addressed at the hearing of this application can be stated as follows:
1. Burden of proof;
2. Validity of the disclaimers relating to the '446 Patent;
3. Validity of the patent on the basis of one or more of the following:
a) obviousness;
b) anticipation;
c) the relevant claims being broader then the invention made or disclosed; and
d) a failure to meet the requirements of the legislation;
